        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/51698",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=maks3w",
                        "name": "maks3w",
                        "displayName": "Maks 3w",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I guess that is something related with the last \":\" in [fd35:4776:6804:2:2:]\r\n\r\nI need to read the RFC for to know if is valid that",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=maks3w",
                        "name": "maks3w",
                        "displayName": "Maks 3w",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-08-24T08:14:37.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-08-24T08:14:37.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/51704",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=diemuzi",
                        "name": "diemuzi",
                        "displayName": "Sammie S. Taunton",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I should of added that the URL I'm accessing is [fd35:4776:6804:2:2::2]. Something I hadn't noticed the logs did not show.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=diemuzi",
                        "name": "diemuzi",
                        "displayName": "Sammie S. Taunton",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-08-24T13:35:25.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-08-24T13:35:25.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/51725",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=heiglandreas",
                        "name": "heiglandreas",
                        "displayName": "Andreas Heigl",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "As far as I see it, the Zend\\Uri\\Uri::setHost already gets the trunkated IP-Address as parameter as the Exception states \"[fd35:4776:6804:2:2:]\" as the problematic IP. This is the IP-That gets submitted as Parameter.\r\n\r\nI've found a part in Zend\\Http\\PhpEnvironment\\Request::setServer() where the port gets removed from the Server 'name' 'when $_SERVER['SERVER_NAME'] is not set'. Why this is happening only with your Safari-Browser I currently can not tell as my Safari does not behave like that. Which Safari-Version do you use? When I get that, I can dig into this further.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=heiglandreas",
                        "name": "heiglandreas",
                        "displayName": "Andreas Heigl",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-08-27T09:11:08.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-08-27T09:11:08.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/51727",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=diemuzi",
                        "name": "diemuzi",
                        "displayName": "Sammie S. Taunton",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Safari Version: 5.1.7 (7534.57.2) Windows 7\r\n\r\nBecause I don't know if you know how IPv6 addresses work I'll just mention this. Keep in mind I'm accessing the IPv6 address of [fd35:4776:6804:2:2::2]. Notice there is no port number here, otherwise it would be written as [fd35:4776:6804:2:2::2]:80. The long version of this address would look like this [fd35:4776:6804:0002:0002:0000:0000:0002]. I have tried this as well but the results are the same.\r\n\r\nAs an additional test I setup an actual hostname and pointed it to this IP Address and Safari works. So that at least rules out any coding problems I may have caused for this to happen which I am unaware about.\r\n\r\nI also tried an IPv4 address and it works too.\r\n\r\nMy only guess is that somewhere it's taking the : or :: in the IPv6 address and treating it like a port number, where-as it should not.\r\n\r\nAs stated before, I'm willing to help out as much as I can. Just hope I didn't push anyone's buttons by my IPv6 statement above.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=diemuzi",
                        "name": "diemuzi",
                        "displayName": "Sammie S. Taunton",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-08-27T15:06:14.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-08-27T15:06:14.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/51728",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=heiglandreas",
                        "name": "heiglandreas",
                        "displayName": "Andreas Heigl",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Can you give us a var_dump of the $_SERVER-variable? I'm guessing, that some part of that array is missing and therefore the setServer-method does some magic that does not give the correct results. But to make that clear, we would need the var_dump. Actually it's just whether the key 'SERVER_NAME' is present or not.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=heiglandreas",
                        "name": "heiglandreas",
                        "displayName": "Andreas Heigl",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-08-27T15:27:16.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-08-27T15:27:16.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/51729",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=diemuzi",
                        "name": "diemuzi",
                        "displayName": "Sammie S. Taunton",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Here are two vardumps so you have something to compare:\r\n\r\n# Firefox\r\nhttp:\/\/pastebin.com\/WTVHLNzg\r\n\r\n# Safari\r\nhttp:\/\/pastebin.com\/jfwa6j09",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=diemuzi",
                        "name": "diemuzi",
                        "displayName": "Sammie S. Taunton",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-08-27T15:33:53.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-08-27T15:33:53.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/51730",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=heiglandreas",
                        "name": "heiglandreas",
                        "displayName": "Andreas Heigl",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I found the cause of the issue.\r\n\r\nThe var_Dumps you provided showed the following lines:\r\n\r\nFirefox: \r\n[\"SERVER_NAME\"]=> string(19) \"zf2.sitegoodies.net\"\r\n[\"SERVER_ADDR\"]=> string(21) \"fd35:4776:6804:2:2::2\"\r\n[\"SERVER_PORT\"]=> string(2) \"80\"\r\n  \r\n\r\nSafari: \r\n[\"SERVER_NAME\"]=> string(21) \"[fd35:4776:6804:2:2:]\"\r\n[\"SERVER_ADDR\"]=> string(21) \"fd35:4776:6804:2:2::2\"\r\n[\"SERVER_PORT\"]=> string(1) \"2\"\r\n\r\nThis shows, that the SERVER_NAME is already broken when sent from Safari to the Server. But that is the value that is used by the Request-Object to feed the host-name (which could be an IP) to the Uri-Object.\r\n\r\nThis seems to be a general PHP-Issue, not a ZF-Issue.\r\n\r\nSorry, but ZF can't know that that is already broken. :-(\r\n\r\n  ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=heiglandreas",
                        "name": "heiglandreas",
                        "displayName": "Andreas Heigl",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-08-27T16:08:31.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-08-27T16:08:31.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/51731",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=diemuzi",
                        "name": "diemuzi",
                        "displayName": "Sammie S. Taunton",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "aha! At least we found it =)\r\n\r\nI was hesitant to even open this bug due to the possibility that it would be a browser issue. In your view, do you think this yields a PHP bug instead?\r\n\r\nThank you for taking the time to check this out =)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=diemuzi",
                        "name": "diemuzi",
                        "displayName": "Sammie S. Taunton",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-08-27T16:11:54.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-08-27T16:11:54.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/51733",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=maks3w",
                        "name": "maks3w",
                        "displayName": "Maks 3w",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I guess that we must put a special case for Safari. [~matthew] Thoughts?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=maks3w",
                        "name": "maks3w",
                        "displayName": "Maks 3w",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-08-27T19:24:41.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-08-27T19:24:41.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/51734",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I think a special case where the user agent is known and we have something looking like an IPv6 address might make sense -- if it has happened once, it may happen again. ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-08-27T19:40:16.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-08-27T19:40:16.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/51743",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=maks3w",
                        "name": "maks3w",
                        "displayName": "Maks 3w",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Fix with path https:\/\/github.com\/zendframework\/zf2\/pull\/2249\r\n\r\nCredits to heiglandreas ",
